      "transcript_segment": "begin in the second quarter. Due to actions to mitigate tariffs and recovery of transitory impacts from Win Now. We expect earnings to be flattish. With gross margins beginning to reflect. And disciplined SG&A management. Setting the foundation for earnings recovery from there. We also recognize that the environment around us has become increasingly dynamic. And we could experience unplanned volatility due to the disruption in the Middle East. Rising oil prices. And other factors that could impact. Either input costs or consumer behavior. We are focused on what we can control. And these assumptions reflect the macro environment as it stands today. Now [snorts] I'll share a specific outlook for the fourth quarter of fiscal 26. We expect revenues in Q4 to be down 2 to 4%. With modest growth in North America despite lapping a value liquidation in the prior year. Largely offset by declines in Greater China and Converse. We expect Greater China to be down approximately 20% in the fourth quarter. Reflecting reduced selling that we highlighted last quarter. As well as accelerated actions to clean up the marketplace. We anticipate a two-point benefit from foreign exchange. We expect sequential improvement in gross margin. With Q4 down approximately 25 to 75 basis points. Including 250 basis points due to higher tariffs in North America. We expect Q4 SG&A dollars to be flat to down slightly. We expect other expense net of interest income. To be an expense of 15 to 25 million in the fourth quarter. And we expect our full year tax rate to be in the low 20% range. And last. We will return to providing full year and long-term guidance at our investor day in the fall. With that, I'll pass it back to Elliott. Thanks Matt. Before we move to your questions. I want to leave you with an image that stayed with me from this quarter. I was in Barcelona Barcelona meeting with athletes and leaders from FC Barcelona. A partner of ours since 1998. And I stood on the pitch at Camp Nou. If you've ever been there. You know it is more than a stadium. It is one of the most imposing stages in sport. A place built for pressure. Belief and unforgettable moments. And right now Camp Nou tells another story too. Above the pitch, there is scaffolding. In the corners, there are cranes. Entire sections are unfinished. The stadium is being rebuilt tier by tier, piece by piece. To accommodate over 100,000 supporters. The work is still underway. Capacity right now is limited. And it requires patience and perseverance. And still the supporters are in full voice. The players are still stepping onto the pitch focused on competing. And winning. And all around them. The work is transforming what their home. Their club. Will become. What stayed with me was the reality of both things being true at once. Competing today. While building for tomorrow.",
      "transcript_segment_ko": "2분기부터는 관세 완화 조치 및 Win Now 일시적 영향 회복으로 이익이 보합세로 안정될 것으로 예상합니다. Q4 가이던스: 매출 2~4% 감소, 북미는 소폭 성장이나 Greater China(-20%)·Converse 하락으로 상쇄됩니다. 관세 영향으로 Q4 총이익률에 250bp 역풍이 있으며, SG&A는 소폭 감소 또는 보합. FY26 연간 및 장기 가이던스는 가을 투자자의 날에 제시할 예정입니다. CEO Elliott Hill은 공사 중인 FC 바르셀로나 캄프 누를 비유로 들었습니다. 100,000석 규모로 재건 중인 경기장에서 선수들은 여전히 그 위에서 경기합니다. '오늘 경기하면서 내일을 위해 재건 중'이라는 메시지로 나이키의 현재를 정의했습니다.",
